  <h1>
   draw_get_alpha
  </h1>
  This function returns the current value of the draw alpha, which will range between 0 (fully transparent) and 1 (fully opaque). The draw alpha affects the transparency of all draw functions, and can be set with the
  <span>
   <a href="draw_set_alpha.htm">
    draw_set_alpha()
   </a>
  </span>
  function.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">draw_get_alpha()
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">var _cur_alpha = draw_get_alpha();
draw_set_alpha(text_alpha);
draw_text(x, y, text);
draw_set_alpha(_cur_alpha);
</code></pre>
  The above code stores the current draw alpha into a local variable, and changes the draw alpha based on an instance variable. After drawing some text, it resets the alpha back to the value stored in the local variable.
 </body>
